Here are 15 factual question-answer pairs based on the provided document page:

1. Q: What is the purpose of a Führungszeugnis (Personal ID)?
A: It serves as proof of identity and can be used for various official purposes.

2. Q: Who can apply for an Erweitertes Führungszeugnis (Extended ID)?
A: Anyone who needs additional information on their ID, such as employment history or education records.

3. Q: What is the difference between a Behördliches Führungszeugnis (Official ID) and a Privatrechtliches Führungszeugnis (Personal ID)?
A: An official ID is used for government purposes, while a personal ID is used for private matters.

4. Q: How can I obtain an Europäisches Führungszeugnis (European ID)?
A: By applying through the Bundesamt für Justiz (Federal Justice Agency) online system or at a Hamburg Service location.

5. Q: What are the requirements for obtaining an Erweitertes Führungszeugnis?
A: The applicant must provide additional information, such as employment history, education records, or proof of financial dependency on a minor.

6. Q: Can I apply for an Erweitertes Führungszeugnis online?
A: Yes, through the Bundesamt für Justiz (Federal Justice Agency) online system.

7. Q: What is the purpose of the Speed Capture Terminal at Hamburg Service locations?
A: To facilitate biometric data collection for ID applications, such as fingerprints and photographs.

8. Q: How much does it cost to use the Speed Capture Terminal?
A: The fee is 6.00 EUR per photo.

9. Q: Can I use the Speed Capture Terminal for Fischereischeine (Fishing Permits) or Führerscheinanträge (Driver's License Applications)?
A: No, these applications require a different type of biometric data.

10. Q: How long does it take to process an Erweitertes Führungszeugnis application?
A: The processing time varies depending on the complexity of the application and the workload of the Hamburg Service office.

11. Q: Can I obtain an Erweitertes Führungszeugnis if I have a criminal record?
A: Yes, but the applicant must provide additional information and may be subject to stricter requirements or delays.

12. Q: What is the purpose of the Bundeszentralregister (Federal Register) in relation to Führungszeugsnisse?
A: It serves as a central database for ID records and provides information on applicants' criminal history.

13. Q: Can I apply for an Erweitertes Führungszeugnis if I am under 18 years old?
A: Yes, but the applicant must provide additional documentation and meet specific requirements.

14. Q: How do I know if my application for an Erweitertes Führungszeugnis is approved or rejected?
A: You will receive a written notification from the Hamburg Service office indicating the outcome of your application.

15. Q: Can I appeal a rejection of my application for an Erweitertes Führungszeugnis?
A: No, as per the Rechtsbehelf (Legal Remedy) section of the document, there is no appeal process for rejected applications.